The paper deals with biomedical image segmentation using deep learning and active learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of uncertainty and similarity information, which falls under the scope of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves formulating a generalized version of the maximum set cover problem, which is a combinatorial optimization problem, indicating that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also deals with biomedical image analysis, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
